  37,101,So We gave him good news of a forbearing son
  37,102,"Then when the boy reached the age to work with him, Abraham said, ‚ÄúO my dear son! I have seen in a dream that I ňĻmustňļ sacrifice you. So tell me what you think.‚ÄĚ He replied, ‚ÄúO my dear father! Do as you are commanded. God willing, you will find me steadfast.‚ÄĚ"
  37,103,"Then when they submitted ňĻto God‚Äôs Willňļ, and Abraham laid him on the side of his forehead ňĻfor sacrificeňļ"
